Ahmed Lawan By Muhammad Bashir President of the Senate, Ahmed Lawan, on Saturday sought the support of Jigawa delegates ahead of the presidential primary of the All Progressives Congress (APC). Lawan, an APC presidential aspirant, said he possessed all the required experiences to lead Nigeria into greatness, if given the mandate in 2023. “I’ve served at the National Assembly for 23 years which enables me to acquire lots of experience that can guide me to lead Nigeria to greater height,” Lawan said. He, therefore, urged the delegates to give him their votes at the presidential primary election. The senate president also promised to address the security challenges bedeviling the country, particularly in the North. “Even though the present administration under president Muhammad Buhari has done and is still doing well in tackling security challenges, I assure you that if I become the next president of this country, I will build on that. ”I will provide the security agencies with the necessary equipment to enable them end the security challenges,” he said. In his remarks, Gov. Muhammad Badaru, represented by his Deputy, Alhaji Umar Namadi, described the aspirant as an experienced and dependable lawmaker. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Lawan also visited Emir of Dutse, Dr Nuhu Muhammad, to seek his blessing for his ambition to become the next president of Nigeria. (NAN) (www.nannews.ng) Edited by Vincent Obi/Julius Toba-Jegede